  "updated_summary": "A woman with short curly dark hair, identified as 39 and a 'geriatric mum,' shared her personal experience of needing a father for her child, noting friends also had children in their early 40s, with animated text reinforcing her age and label. A woman with reddish-brown hair recounted a seven-year journey with six miscarriages before conceiving at 41, a detail also shown in text. An animated infographic presented data from ABS Labour Force Status of Families 2022, stating '1m Single parent families' were recorded last year, with '4 out of 5 lead by women.' The woman with short curly dark hair, now in a geometric-patterned wrap dress, expressed a desire for more affordable childcare, better employer support for remote work, and government subsidies, with text stating 'I wish childcare wasn’t so expensive.' Later, the woman with reddish-brown hair emphasized the need for financial support systems for women returning to careers and addressed childcare issues, accompanied by text 'Support systems need to be there.' A woman with short light brown hair explained that society, built by a patriarchy, is not well-established to support women during maternity leave or fathers who want to care for their children, leading to low fertility rates as Australia becomes more expensive, with text overlays like 'not well established to support women' and 'support fathers.' The woman with short curly dark hair humorously declared, 'I don't know how I do another kid actually without going completely demented,' stressing that 'Parenthood is like, almost impossible here in Australia. We just don't have the support,' with text highlighting 'IT’S TOUGH' and 'Parenthood is like, almost impossible.' A woman with long black hair discussed data from June 2022, noting '3.5 million couple families without dependants,' also known as DINKs. The woman with short light brown hair concluded by reflecting on the world's population reaching 8 billion, remarking, 'Feels like there's a lot of people on our little planet.'"
